==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*ajja-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[ei]] (Dutch [[ei]]), Old High German [[ei]] (German [[Ei]]), Old Norse [[egg]] (English [[egg]], Swedish [[ägg]]).  The Germanic source is probably related to Greek [[ωον|ᾠόν]], Latin [[ovum]] (French [[oeuf]]), Welsh [[wy]], Old Church Slavonic [[айьце]] (Russian [[яйцо]]).

